title: For Sale:  Normalized Yugo Zastava AK47 Rifle Like New, 1000/rd TulAmmoTrade Bitcoin
postcontent: For $600 in Bitcoin or cash, is 1000 rounds of TulAmmo 7.62x39 and one Zastava Yugo AK-47 in like new condition. Will sell the rifle and ammo separately, for $500 for the rifle, or $200 for the ammo. Has fired maybe 50 rounds. This rifle was originally equipped with all the things to keep us safe, including the restricted magazine. Normalizing the Yugo isn't easy, but I liked the swept gas nut, the other models don't have and the beefer construction. Hogging-out the well with a Dremel looks terrible and is just the beginning of a proper conversion. They cut the bolt as well, and it must be replaced to feed correctly. Conversion to normal capacity magazines, threaded barrel and other things not remembered, were performed by Two-Riivers Arms, owned by Rep. Steve Russell. Two-Rivers specializes in recreations of the Tabuk, if I recall. I was lucky an AK-only shop was not far. I wanted a correct and pristine conversion of the magazine well, and that's what I got. It looks and works perfect. To do it right, it all had to be drilled apart, machined and reassembled. The bolt and gas piston was replaced along with the trigger group. The top cover was replaced, to remove the ridiculous useless rail mounted to the shakey sheet-metal dust cover of an AK, by the importer. Parts removed in the conversion are included.
